# Project Rules — Nheko Patch Management

## CRITICAL: Only modify patch files, never nheko source

This project maintains patches for the [nheko](nheko/) Matrix client. The [`nheko/`](nheko/) directory contains the upstream source code and **MUST NOT be modified directly**.

### When fixing build issues or making changes:
- **NEVER** modify `.cpp`, `.h`, `.qml`, `.cmake`, or any other files inside [`nheko/`](nheko/)
- **ONLY** modify `.patch` files inside [`patches/`](patches/)
- If a change would logically touch a file in [`nheko/`](nheko/), instead update the corresponding patch file in [`patches/`](patches/) that introduces that change
- New source files should be placed in [`patches/new-files/`](patches/new-files/) preserving the original relative path structure
- Plans and documentation go in [`plans/`](plans/)

### Patch file naming convention:
- [`patches/0000-unified-nhekobeep.patch`](patches/0000-unified-nhekobeep.patch) — Unified beep patch
- [`patches/000X-description.patch`](patches/000X-description.patch) — Individual feature/fix patches
- [`patches/new-files/`](patches/new-files/) — New files to be introduced by patches
- [`patches/archive/`](patches/archive/) — Deprecated/archived patches
